understand and couldn't articulate.

00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:03.990
Why did my grandfather
have to work so hard?

00:04:03.990 --> 00:04:06.750
Why, as a result of
the work that he did,

00:04:06.750 --> 00:04:10.550
did he get sick and die so young?

00:04:14.060 --> 00:04:18.410
My, I mean, all families
are mysterious, aren't they?

00:04:18.410 --> 00:04:21.130
My folks split up when
I was young, so I was --

00:04:21.130 --> 00:04:25.630
and I was one of those -- I
was the only person I knew,

00:04:25.630 --> 00:04:31.090
the only kid I knew that was
from a broken family in that way.

00:04:31.090 --> 00:04:33.260
And yet my family was not broken.

00:04:33.260 --> 00:04:36.410
My grandparents were
there, my aunts and uncles,

00:04:36.410 --> 00:04:38.350
and my cousins were there.

00:04:38.350 --> 00:04:42.530
And so I was, as a kid, you
know, growing up, you know,

00:04:42.530 --> 00:04:46.330
from being a small
boy to being a 17,

00:04:46.330 --> 00:04:51.760 position:56%
18-year-old when I left Gloversville
to go to the university,

00:04:51.760 --> 00:04:54.560
