way answers to questions

00:04:59.580 --> 00:05:01.860
that don't have answers, really.

00:05:01.860 --> 00:05:05.920
And that's part of the mystery
and the wonder of childhood

00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:09.900
as you ask yourself these, without
even articulating them exactly,

00:05:09.900 --> 00:05:15.290
you ask yourself these questions
that do not have answers.

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:19.590 position:56%
As I say, later on, you know, you go
to the university, you read books,

00:05:19.590 --> 00:05:23.170
you become more sophisticated,
and --

00:05:23.170 --> 00:05:27.470
and there is all that
repetition, as I said.

00:05:27.470 --> 00:05:34.680
But the effect of that is to make
you feel like you know something.

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:37.660
&gt;&gt; Don't.

00:05:37.660 --> 00:05:38.960
&gt;&gt; You don't.

00:05:38.960 --> 00:05:40.680
&gt;&gt; The older you get,
the more you know, right?

00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:41.980
&gt;&gt; You don't.

00:05:41.980 --> 00:05:43.280
You don't.

00:05:43.280 --> 00:05:47.860 position:56%
And, and so we have more knowledge
as we grow older, but for me anyway,

00:05:47.860 --> 00:05:51.890 position:56%
